What is W3C WebDriver Protocol?

W3C WebDriver Protocol ek standard protocol hai jo Selenium WebDriver aur browsers ke beech communication ko define karta hai.

Is protocol ko World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) ne standardize kiya hai.
Selenium 4 se WebDriver isi protocol ka use karta hai.

Simple words me:

W3C WebDriver protocol defines how Selenium commands are sent from the test script to the browser driver and how the browser performs those actions.
-----------------------
Test Script
     ↓
Selenium Client Library
     ↓
W3C WebDriver Protocol (HTTP Request)
     ↓
Browser Driver (ChromeDriver / GeckoDriver)
     ↓
Browser
---------------------------------
Example:
Agar aap code likhte ho

driver.get("https://google.com");

To Selenium ek HTTP request send karta hai browser driver ko, aur browser driver browser ko command execute karne bolta hai.

----------------------
Why W3C WebDriver Protocol is Important

1️⃣ Standardization
Sab browsers ek hi standard follow karte hain.

2️⃣ Better Cross-Browser Compatibility
Chrome, Firefox, Edge sab easily support karte hain.

3️⃣ No JSON Wire Protocol Issues
Selenium 3 me JSON Wire Protocol use hota tha jo different browsers me inconsistent tha.

4️⃣ More Stable Automation
Commands predictable aur stable ho gaye hain.

------------------------------
Selenium Version Difference
Selenium Version	Protocol Used
Selenium 3	JSON Wire Protocol
Selenium 4	W3C WebDriver Protocol
--------------------------------------------
W3C WebDriver Protocol is a standard protocol defined by the World Wide Web Consortium that allows Selenium WebDriver 
to communicate with browsers using HTTP requests.
Selenium 4 uses this protocol instead of the JSON Wire Protocol to ensure better standardization and cross-browser compatibility.

